<br>
The 80% 'rule' is so funny, we should reverse it and give warriors 80% of a knights utility, or even go with 95% of a knights utility to compensate for the 95% tanking ability compared to a warrior. Thats where the imbalance lies, knights have 95% of a warriors tanking ability and HP's and they get oogles of 'utility' to compensate for the miniscule differences while warriors gain nothing but that whopping 5% edge.<br>
<br>
So to summarize a knight with 95% of a warriors tanking ability and HP's + 1beeelion% of a warriors utility(can even use 40-60% of other parent class ie cleric / nec if you would like)  does not = 100%<br>
<br>
Now how to fix it? <br>
Take away /disc defensive, its been fucking us since day one. 'But you get defensive! please, please take it away.<br>
<br>
Give warriors 20% innate mitigation. I should never be hit for as much as you, period. lets hardcode the 80% rule shall we.<br>
<br>
Make taunt work and associate a hate value with it. Why would it be so game breaking that a warrior could hold agro when a knight can right now and theres no problem with it? Knights would still add heals, stuns, root, snare, mana taps, attack taps, etc etc etc<br>
<br>
Give warriors battle cries or something similar as utility. ie. Cry of Zek lvl 65 +50ac +50attk +5dmg bonus group only duration 3min reuse 10min, or special abilities / attacks ie. Headbutt only works from front 180 arc stuns mob for 1sec and lowers parry / riposte rate of the mob for a 15sec duration since he has blood and tears in his eyes, 1min reuse. Or anything like these.<br>
<br>
And with all the bandage aa I have I want mummify aa ability which would be a rez! Not seriously though.<br>
<br>
I'm not a big fan of raising hp's even more, like it would even matter when CH only heals 7500-9375?hps. My magelo would look cool and thats about it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=paeneq>Paen EQ</A> at: 11/11/03 2:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyradin>Cyradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#330000>(11/11/03 3:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1055.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Cry to Arms!</span><hr size=1> Daramin is making alotta good points as to what the problems are, it shows a great amount of knowledge about the game and about the way his class works.  But i see Baldrik giving some great info on possible fixes.  Good luck Warriors, I hope to see something positive in your near future. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7106" target="top">Master Cyradin The Sarcastic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
