<br>
Yes it does trivialise the XP game, and no I don't die in XP groups unless half the group go LD at once.  That's why I don't do experience groups any more; they are boring and trivial unless you go out of your way to make them otherwise.<br>
<br>
Even if you DO die, and have a completely nightmare wipe way deep in a zone with no way of getting to your corpse, you can just AFK for 20 minutes and have your body delivered back to you.  No risk, lots of XP reward.  Boring boring boring.<br>
<br>
Frankly, if you have mobs that are giving you 2% of an AA per kill in a group setting, those mobs should pose a significant danger to your group and you should not be able to breeze through them half-AFK the whole time with nary a worry.  Pull mob, slow mob, aggro lock mob to tank, beat mob down.  Go pull another.  Never ever get an add unless the puller screws up, and even if he does then almost all the mobs are mezzable so it doesn't matter anyway.  Boring boring boring.  The concept of EXPERIENCE was supposed to be that you gained experience by killing something that was a challenge, that actually tested your capabilities and tactics.  That's all out the window, and it is EXACTLY things like aggro lock, the free availability of insane mana regen, the free availability of huge slows and trivial crowd control that dumbed down the game so much; and it SUCKS.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
