<br>
So, if you're not going to change the balance one way, you have to change it the other way. I appreciate what you're saying Porte about that level of agro making xp groups trivial. At the risk of repeating myself, though, that horse is already out of the barn -- if you close the door now on Warriors you're basically saying that the class is doomed. I won't accept that, and I know many other people who play Warriors -- and even plenty of people who play other classes -- feel the same way I do.<br>
<br>
Basically, it has to be fixed. It won't be fixed by a nerf. Therefore Warriors will need to be buffed. If I get too bored with normal adventures, I'll switch to hard. If those are boring, well, at least Verant will have the *same* problem to fix for all three of their tank classes. Can you imagine what it would do to Warriors if they tried to introduce xp situations that Knights find challenging with an appropriate level of reward to match the increased risk? We'd be completely screwed. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89897">Daramin Anklebiter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
