<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As a Paladin I broadly agree with Boanerges regarding the problem, at least at pre-elemental levels (elemental and Time equipped Warriors have absolutely zero problems with aggro). However nerfing stun aggro is, I believe a non-starter. Stuns were given aggro specifically to prevent Clerics, Wizards etc from locking down mobs without worrying about aggro, and changing that to &quot;solve&quot; the tanking issue would cause more problems than it would address. Quite apart from that it wouldn't have any effect at all on SKs, who are just as great at aggro generation as Paladins are. <br>
<br>
I actually believe the nerf to Knight mitigation is a better idea. As I've said before, leaving Knights as aggro masters is fine as long as there is a real survivability downside to using a Knight as a tank. That gives you two tanking methods available for the XP group to choose from - a great meatshield you have to watch aggro around, or an aggro magnet you need to work harder to keep alive. Correctly balanced, that would be absolutely ideal, and maintain class distinctions. <br>
<br>
Of course, none of this addresses the much bigger problem of casters vs melee. I am always amazed people concentrate so heavily on the Knight/Warrior issue - real though it is - and largely ignore the amazing overpowerment pure casters have over everyone else. Maybe that's just been thrown into the &quot;too hard&quot; pile.....<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So don't assume that we're all just out for ourselves.  I want an unbroken game, and if that means nerfing me - as long as it's done as part of a PROPER rebalancing - that's fine by me.<br>
