In retrospect, I feel for them when I see them in a group with me and the best they can do when a mob is inc is whack it with an arrow, the slower slows and there goes aggro. Taunt weapons are great, but lets face it, you can't click the effect, not like a stun, so now you have to rely on high dex and hope. I say give warriors taunt effect more power. A warriors taunt should = the aggro of a stun in my opinion. I mean, that is their job, /taunt, /kick get aggro hold aggro. Give them some kind of edge in thier jobs... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/normlnuk/myhomepage/my%20sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnipgnoppikpok>Gnipgnop Pikpok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Yucky, yet Yummy</span><br>  Posts: 859<br> <font color=#330000>(11/15/03 11:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1055.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/88/88432/pages/316024/ghandi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Cry to Arms!</span><hr size=1> It is nice to be THE tank...but face it no matter which class ends up being THE tank there is still a matter of too many tanks for not enough demand. Even if Paladins disappeared off the face of the planet and the only tanks were warriors there would still be extra warriors not tanking that would need a group. It matters not the name, warrior, sk, paladin, there is still too much supply and not enough demand. There needs to be an alternative utilty need for all of them so that there is a need for any of them in a group EVEN if the group already has a tank. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/88/88432/pages/319302/211b.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
